  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a quiet, upscale office with tall sheer curtains filtering daylight across the room. An older bald man with light skin sits in a black leather armchair, dressed in a gray suit, white shirt, and dark tie. His legs are crossed and he holds an open black folder or binder on his lap, reading and speaking calmly. Around him are modern office furnishings: a low wooden coffee table with papers, a black leather sofa or chair to the left, a small round side table with a black-shaded lamp and a small gold clock, and a dark wooden desk off to the right. The walls are dark green and textured, giving the room a formal executive feel.\n\nAs the man continues, the GEICO gecko appears near him, first as a small green blur in the foreground and then clearly standing upright on the arm of a black leather chair. The gecko is a tiny animated lizard with bright green skin, a pale cream-colored belly, large rounded eyes, and orange markings on top of his head. He stands like a person, facing the seated man, while the man looks toward him with an easy, conversational expression. The gecko remains poised on the chair arm, listening and reacting, while the man sits back with one arm resting on the chair.\n\nThe scene then shifts to a busy mailroom or office processing area. The gecko stands on a gray worktable, dwarfed by a large clear cylindrical mail canister with beige caps at both ends. He grips and wrestles with the canister, which is almost as tall as he is and much wider, tipping it from side to side as he tries to position it beneath a clear overhead pneumatic tube. In the background, office workers in light shirts and khaki pants sort papers and packages near shelves filled with mail trays. On the tabletop nearby are stacked envelopes and folders, a white plastic spoon, a white cup, and small office tools.\n\nThe gecko continues maneuvering the heavy-looking canister, pushing it upright under the vertical tube. Once aligned, the canister is pulled upward into the clear tube above him, leaving the gecko standing alone on the tabletop. He looks up toward where it disappeared, then relaxes with his small arms at his sides amid the mailroom activity behind him.\n\nThe view returns to a close-up of the gecko against the softly lit curtain background. He speaks while making small expressive hand gestures, lifting one hand beside his face and then bringing both hands together near his chest. His large eyes and slight smile give him a thoughtful, confident expression.\n\nThe commercial ends on a plain white screen with the blue GEICO logo centered near the top. Beneath it, in blue, is “geico.com,” and below that in black is the phone number “1-800-947-AUTO.”",
